    en: "NY licenses funeral directors and funeral firms under Public Health Law Article 34. The NY Department of Health Bureau of Funeral Directing reviews licenses and handles complaints. To get licensed, a funeral director needs an associate degree in funeral service, a 12-month supervised residency, and a passing score on national and state exams. Funeral firms must be owned and operated by a licensed funeral director. Misconduct — overcharging, misrepresentation, mishandling of remains, solicitation in hospitals or nursing homes — can lead to license suspension, revocation, civil penalties, or criminal referral. Federal FTC Funeral Rule requires every funeral firm to provide a written General Price List on request — a key consumer right."
